<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,869,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,400,869,894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
The species belongs to a color group showing a dark background and orange to yellow margin that should be thoroughly revised. 
<bibRefCitation author="Prudhoe" box="[650,828,905,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" refString="Prudhoe, S. (1977) Some polyclad turbellarians new to the fauna of the Australian coasts. Records of the Australian Museum, 31 (14), 586 - 604. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.31.1978.205" type="journal article" year="1977">
Prudhoe (
<number box="[762,820,906,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported from Queensland a species with two male gonopores which he misidentified as 
<taxonomicName box="[591,928,941,966]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[591,928,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudoceros flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was listed under single male gonopore 
<taxonomicName box="[269,411,977,1002]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,411,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Laidlaw" box="[526,898,977,1002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" refString="Laidlaw, F. F. (1902) The marine Turbellaria, with an account of the anatomy of some of the species. The Fauna and Geography of the Maldive and Laccadive Archipelagoes, 1 (3), 282 - 312." type="journal article" year="1902" yearSuffix="p">
Laidlaw 
<number box="[633,692,978,1002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1902.0">1902</number>
, p. 
<number box="[743,785,978,1002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="297.0">297</number>
and 
<number box="[852,898,978,1002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="298.0">298</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but Prudhoe’s specimen belongs to a darkbackground 
<taxonomicName box="[293,457,1013,1038]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,457,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudobiceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The description by Prudhoe fits the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Newman &amp; Cannon 1994" authorityName="Newman &amp; Cannon" authorityYear="1994" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="periculosus">
<emphasis box="[981,1284,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudobiceros periculosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Newman" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" refString="Newman, L. J. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1994) Pseudoceros and Pseudobiceros (Platyhelminthes, Polycladida, Pseudocertotidae) from eastern Australia and Papua New Guinea. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 37 (1), 205 - 266." type="journal article" year="1994">
Newman &amp; Cannon 
<number box="[245,302,1050,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in marginal and background color, elongated cerebral eyespots group, and geographical proximity.
</paragraph>
